        <name>disable_caches</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Disables both the data cache and instruction cache. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function calls the Xil_DCacheDisable() and Xil_ICacheDisable() functions to turn off the data and instruction caches, respectively. It is typically used in bare-metal embedded systems where cache coherency is not required or before performing operations that require caches to be disabled. </para>        </detaileddescription>
