        <name>init_uart</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initializes the UART peripheral based on the platform configuration. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function configures the UART for standard output. If the platform uses the 16550 UART, it sets the baud rate and line control register. If the platform uses the PS7 UART, it assumes the bootrom or BSP has already configured it to 115200 bps.</para><para>Platform-specific macros (STDOUT_IS_16550, STDOUT_IS_PS7_UART) determine which initialization steps are performed. </para>        </detaileddescription>
